original: Calvert, Axel Frederick William, direktör, Göteborg, f. 9/9/82 i Gbg av James C. o. Flora Grosse. G. 21 m. Viveka Rosencrantz. Barn: Greger f. 22, stud., Hillevi 24, scriptgirl i Europa Fiim, Sthlm, Madeleine 26. — Prakt. o. stud. i Engl. o. Tyskl. Förest. f. Billeruds sulfitfabr. 05-07, anst. v. A-B Calvert & Co. i Gbg sed. 08, verkst. dir. där sed. 23. Medl. av SFMK sed. 21.
translated: Calvert, Axel Frederick William, director, Gothenburg, born on September 9, 1882 in Gothenburg to James C. and Flora Grosse. Married in 1921 to Viveka Rosencrantz. Children: Greger, born in 1922 and a student, Hillevi, born in 1924 and a scriptgirl in Europa Film in Stockholm, Madeleine, born in 1926. Practiced and studied in England and Germany. Was a manager for Billerud's sulfite factory from 1905 to 1907, then employed by A-B Calvert & Co. in Gothenburg starting in 1908, and became the executive director there in 1923. Was a member of the SFMK from 1921.
